[Result "*"]

1. Nf3{ Although our setup (the Reti Proper) can transpose from other first moves, 1.  Nf3  is the most reliable way to achieve it. }
1. d5
2. c4{ We waste no time challenging Black's early presence in the centre. }
2. c5
3. cxd5{ We should always be happy to capture here when Black can't take back with a pawn of his own. }
3. Qxd5
4. Nc3{ With tempo and already something of a lead in development, one which a quick  d2 - d4  and  e2 - e4  will help to exploit. }
4. Qd8
5. d4
5. e6
6. e4{ Thematic expansion. We might now seize further space with  d4 - d5  and have no objection to an early exchange of queens. }
6. cxd4
7. Qxd4
7. Qxd4
8. Nxd4{ All of a sudden,  Ndb5  looms as Black begins to look a little vulnerable on  c7 . }
8. a6
9. Nb3{ Black has kept us out of  b5 , but remains clearly worse.     After  Be3  and  Rc1  it's not hard to envision his queenside creaking quite loudly, be that after  Nc5  or  Na4 , as we'll cover in the rare 2nd moves chapter.  }
