2. Nf6
3. cxd5
3. Nxd5
4. e4{ Seizing space and with tempo as we prepare to boss the centre. }
4. Nb6
5. d4{ Constructing an ideal centre and just where is Black's counterplay? }
5. e6
6. Nc3{ Knights before bishops is by no means our mantra, but here such a policy works well. White will now bring the light-squared bishop to a decent location on  d3 , then castle. }
6. Be7
7. Bd3
7. O-O
8. O-O{ Already attacking ideas after  e4 - e5 , even involving  Qe2 - e4 , are high on the agenda and Black was rather crushed in Euwe-Matisons , World Amateur Championship, The Hague 1928. }
