6. Nc6
7. O-O( { White waits for Black's bishop to appear on  d6 , only wanting to exchange on  c5  when doing so comes with tempo. In general we're quite happy to meet  ...cxd4  with  Nxd4 , but here }7...cxd4 8.exd4!? { is actually quite tempting, look to obtain an early initiative down the e-file and against  c6  with  Ne5  top of the agenda. } )
7. Bd6
8. dxc5{ Naturally we exchange when doing so comes with tempo. }
8. Bxc5
9. Nc3{ Exerting a bit of pressure on  d5  ahead of carrying out the queenside fianchetto. }
9. O-O
10. b3
10. Bg4
