8. Bb7
9. Bd3{ White's ideal set-up. We will make the king quite safe on  g1  and find a good role for the queen's rook on  c1 . }
9. c5
10. O-O
10. Nbd7
11. Rc1{ Black is pretty solid in this Queen's Indian-type position, but the central tension still makes his life a little unpleasant.     White may increase the central pressure with  Qe2  and  Rfd1 , after which  Ba6  is one plan,  Bf5  another, looking to target Black's centre with  dxc5 , a policy  Na4  may exploit. Note too that White may instead unfurl the bishop on  b2  with  Ne2 , moving that piece towards the kingside, as well as very much consider the good, old plan of  Ne5  and  f2 - f4 . We'll explore the resulting positions in the 6... b6  lines.  }
