1. Nf3{ Although our setup (the Reti Proper) can transpose from other first moves, 1.  Nf3  is the most reliable way to achieve it. }
1. d5
2. c4{ We waste no time challenging Black's early presence in the centre. }
2. c6
3. e3{ Taking control of  d4  and so enabling White to safely bring the queen's knight out to  c3 . }
3. Nf6
4. Nc3{ Bringing the second knight to a good location, while keeping White's options open. We won't make Black's day by transposing straight into main-line Slav waters with  d2 - d4 , but may well make good use of the  b3 -square for the queen or b-pawn. }
4. e6
5. b3( { We've no desire to enter Semi-Slav waters with }5.d4 { , }{ but may still be able to menace some early aggression. First though it's important to untangle the queenside with our favourite Reti fianchetto. } )
5. Bd6
