8. e5
9. cxd5( { Ever a good retort to the ambitious, early advance and now White is once again ready to cause early trouble if }9...cxd5?! 10.Nb5 { . } )
9. Nxd5
10. Ne4{ Activating the knight with tempo, while unfurling the potentially powerful bishop on  b2 . }
10. Bc7
11. Neg5{ A very direct approach, but the attack on  h7  isn't so easy for Black to prevent and he may also find himself coming under pressure on  f7  after  Ba3  to tickle the rook on  e8 .      Spoiler alert:   the 8... e5  lines  contain some very nice sacrificial ideas for White. }
