8. fxe4
9. hxg4
9. exf3
10. Bb5+{ An important check. We shouldn't forget that White is a pawn down and with  d5  en prise, so developing with tempo is especially useful. }
10. c6
11. dxc6{ Not for the first time White welcomes an exchange of queens, since his king should be safe enough in the centre and  Bf1  is coming once Black has dealt with the large threat of  cxb7 +. }
