3. Qd6
4. c5{ With tempo and this is an advance White should in general always be on the lookout for, aiming to interfere with Black's development. }
4. Qd5
5. e3( { This appears even stronger than }5.Bb2 { . } )( { Now  Nxd4  is threatened and   }5...dxe3 6.fxe3 { followed by  Nc3  would leave White with a handy space advantage and lead in development.     There are also ideas of a timely  Qa4 +, as well as gaining time against the misplaced black queen: } )
