7. exd4
8. Na3{ Once again this is a powerful idea, heading for  b5  or  c2  to pressure  d4 . }
8. Na6
9. Nb5
9. Nxc5
10. Be2{ There's no rush to take on  d4  due to the pin down the long diagonal. }
10. Bd7
11. Bxd4
11. Bxd4
12. Nbxd4{ White was a clear pawn to the good and went on to convert after castling then freeing his d-pawn for active duty in Ronat-Blondel, correspondence 2013. }
