7. d4{ In reversed Blumenfeld fashion, White's strong centre supplies pretty decent compensation. He'll likely complete development with  Bd3 ,  O-O  and then  e3 - e4  and/or  Nbd2 .     Black players have steered clear of this position and no wonder with White controlling the centre and leading in development so. With  Bd3  White will remind Black of the weaknesses created by ... f6 , after which we can complete development with  Nbd2 ,  O-O  and  Qc2 , probing along the  b1 - h7  diagonal. Then  e3 - e4 - e5  may even follow and there can be little doubting White's excellent compensation. }
