6. a6
7. a4
7. axb5
8. cxb5{ A forced recapture here, of course, and now White would again like to support his outside majority from afar with  g2 - g3  and  Bg2 . }
8. c4
9. dxc4
9. e4
10. Nfd2( { A brave, but correct response and not }10.Nxd4? Bb4+ { . The knight will now re-emerge on  b3  unless Black keeps forcing the pace. } )
10. e3
11. fxe3
11. dxe3
12. Ne4{ Another only move, but a good one at that. White absolutely must control the  c3 -square so that he isn't cleaned up by ... Bb4 .     The position isn't entirely clear, but the engines suspect Black may not have quite enough compensation. }
12. Bb4+
13. Nec3{ A fourth fairly forced move in a row as allowing 13.Nbc3?  f5  would not be wise. }
13. Qa5
14. Qd3{ White will get in  Qxe3 + then break the pin with  Bd2 . Black is fairly active and White's position a little ragged, but it will be two extra pawns. }
