18. cxb6( { Now we're threatening to win with   }19.c7+ Bd7 ( 19...Ke7 20.Bc5#  )20.b7! { . } )
18. Bxb4+
19. Nc3{ The queenside duo is once again just too strong with both  c6 - c7 + and  b6 - b7  imminent, as yet again Black's extra rook doesn't even come close to saving him. }( { We're actually following a remarkable game: }19...Qh2 20.b7 ( { The engines point out that the calm }20.c7+!? Kf8 21.Qc6 { is even stronger. } )20...Rb8 21.c7+ Kf8 22.cxb8=Q Qxb8 23.bxc8=Q Qxc8 24.Rg1 { With  g2  falling ( }24...Qh3 25.Qc6 { ), White found himself a piece up and shortly went on to win in Hillarp Persson-Hector, Danish League 2014.     Superb vision and creativity from Tiger! } )
