15. gxh4
16. fxe5{ The engines already assess White's advantage as being close to decisive, and no surprise with  Qd1  and  Rae1  two ideas in the position,  Bxg8  and  exf6  another, and Black having no developed pieces. }
16. f5
17. Rae1{ Bringing the final piece into play. White calmly wants to go  Bb3  then  Nc4  and  Nd6 +, and it's very hard to see Black managing to survive, with White even then likely able to go  Qxd4  to involve the queen. }
