7. b5{ By far the best move, restricting Black's queenside pieces and preparing to bring the light-squared bishop out to  c4 . }
7. Bxc5
8. Bc4{ A great square once again for the bishop and also a move which carries a threat, one which Vishy Anand, no less, failed to appreciate. Yes, forking with 9.  Bxg8   Rxg8  10.  Qc4  is the very much plan. }
8. Ne7
9. exd4{ Again it makes sense to capture so when it comes with tempo and Black surely now doesn't want to relinquish the bishop-pair on  d4 . }
9. exd4
10. Ba3( { An important move, continuing to harry (both }10.Bb2 Bg4 { and }{   }10.O-O Bg4 { have been shown to be much less challenging). } )
10. Bxa3
11. Qxa3( { This recapture so that  ...Bg4  won't threaten structural ruin. Instead, }11.Nxa3 Bg4! 12.Nxd4 Nd7 { looked pretty comfortable for Black in Caruana-Topalov, Saint Louis 2016, whereas now  Nxd4  is a threat and White is also set to castle. } )
11. c6
12. Nxd4{ By now there's nothing better than recouping the pawn and Black should continue to force the pace, not do something slow and allow White to go  O-O  or even  Qg3 . }
12. cxb5
13. Nxb5{ This recapture so that we'll land up with slightly the better minor piece if Black now exchanges ahead of trying to castle. }
13. Bxb5
14. Bxb5+
14. Nbc6
15. O-O( { It's high time to complete development and not err with }15.Bc4? Qd4 { . } )
15. O-O
16. Nc3{ White would now quite like to place the rooks on  b1  and  e1 , after which  Bc4 + would unveil an attack on  b7 . }
16. Nd4
17. Bc4+( { Retaining the bishop looks more challenging than the }17.Rfe1 Nec6 18.Bxc6 Nxc6 { of Ludwig-Klochan, correspondence 2019. } )
17. Kh8
18. Rab1( { Avoiding being forked and while Black is pretty solid here, the position is far from dead. In the long term, Black may face difficulties on the back rank or activating his king, and must also watch over  a5  and especially  b7  }{ ( }18...Ng6 19.Rxb7! { would now be on, with }19...Qc8 { met by }20.Bd5 { ). White will likely overprotect the bishop with  d2 - d3 , activate the other rook via  e1  and maybe even  e4 , with it not beyond the bounds of possibility that one day an attack on  h7  may be possible, such as after  Qc5 - h5 . } )
