19. Rac1( { A new try. White has so far tested }19.Rab1 { in four games that we could find, but after }19...Nd3 20.Bxd3 Qxd3 { Black has excellent chances to draw. }{ It should be said that activating the knights to  b4  or  f5 , as Black has done, might be easy enough for a strong or correspondence player to find, but many amateurs might be concerned that neither knight is entirely secure.     Even after  19. Rac1  Black should be OK, but at least the position isn't dead. One of White's ideas is  Qb1 , covering  d3  while attacking the knight on  f5 , then regrouping with  Bf1  and  a2-a3 . The other is seen if Black does now invade on  d3 : } )
