1. d5
2. c4{ We waste no time challenging Black's early presence in the centre. }
2. dxc4
3. e3
3. Nc6
4. Bxc4{ Against 3... Nc6 , a speciality of the Ukrainian IM Alexander Reprintsev, White can hardly object to his light-squared bishop quickly taking up a powerful role. }
4. e5
5. Nc3( { Straightforward development as White rules out  ...e4 , while not rushing with  d2-d4 . The immediate }5.d4 { has been more popular and is also a good choice, transposing to a sideline of the QGA. Then }5...exd4 6.O-O!? Nf6 7.exd4 { is an IQP position which is fairly pleasant for White with  d4 - d5  on the agenda.     Instead, with 5.  Nc3  White prepares to castle and will also look to get in  d2 - d4  under favourable circumstances, such as if Black develops rather slowly. } )
