8. Be7
9. f4{ This powerful advance left Black struggling for compensation in Langeweg-Romanishin, Amsterdam 1978. White simply wants to regroup with 10.  Qf3  }( { or }9...Nc5 10.Qc6+  ){ after which  O-O ,  b2 - b3  and  Bb2  may follow, with the d-pawn deployed to either  d3  or  d4  depending on how Black sets up (with the queen back on  f3 , ... Nc5 ;  d4  will come with tempo). }
