6. Nc6
7. O-O{ Housing the king while keeping the d-pawn flexible. }
7. Be7
8. Be2( { Heading for a familiar enough set-up after all. If you're happy to grind away on an open board then }8.d4 cxd4 9.Nxd4 Nxd4 10.Bxd4 { is an option followed by  Be2  and  Nc4 , with Anatoly Vaisser's }{   }8.Qe2!? { , }{ intending  Rd1  and only then  d2 - d4 , yet another reasonable approach. } )
