11. Nd5
12. Qc2{ Objectively chances should be about equal, but we would be quite happy with White's reversed Hedgehog set-up, Nowak-Szymczak, Lubniewice 1994. The queen's rook is likely to be developed to  c1 , the king's rook to  d1  or  e1 .     The latter will allow White to consider a possible regrouping with  Bf1 ,  g2 - g3  and  Bg2 ; the former can be followed up with  Qb1  and  Qa1 , placing the queen on Richard Reti's favourite square for it, here increasing the pressure down the long diagonal while supporting the  d3 - d4  advance. }
