13. Ne2{ Keeping pieces on and Black's counterplay under control. }
13. Qa5
14. Nfd4{ White prepares to land the knight on  f5  and also refuses to fear Black's queenside exchanging plan. }
14. Ba3
15. Bxa3
15. Qxa3
16. f3( { This does slightly weaken  e3 , but removes the slightly annoying knight from  e4 , while hoping for }16...Nc3? 17.Nxc3 Rxc3 18.Nb5 { . } )
16. Ng5
17. Qd2{ With Black's counterplay under control and  Rac1  then  Rfd1  on their way, White enjoyed a stable plus in Khenkin-Luther, Osterburg 2006. }
