1. Nf3{ Although our setup (the Reti Proper) can transpose from other first moves, 1.  Nf3  is the most reliable way to achieve it. }
1. d5
2. c4{ We waste no time challenging Black's early presence in the centre. }
2. e6
3. e3
3. c5
4. cxd5
4. exd5
5. d4{ Transposing to a line of the Tarrasch Defence as we play to gradually take control and leave Black with a long-term weakness on  d5 . }( { If now }5...a6 { we’ll see }6.Nc3 { (threatening to take on  c5  then  d5 ) }6...Nf6 7.b3 { via a }{   }3...Nf6 4.Nc3 a6 5.b3 c5 6.cxd5 exd5 7.d4 { move order. } )
5. Nf6
