9. Be7
10. Na4( { Vladimir Kramnik was content to go }10.dxc5 Bxc5 11.b3 { here, but we can also be a little more ambitious. } )( { White threatens to take on  c5  and after }10...cxd4 11.exd4 { will be quick to increase the pressure with  Ne5  and/ or  Qc2 . } )
10. c4
11. Ne5{ Expanding with tempo ahead of challenging the advanced point on  c4 . }
11. Qc7
12. b3
12. cxb3
13. axb3{ Black is already clearly worse with  Qc2  and  Ba3  set to exacerbate his problems down the c-file. }
