12. a5
13. Nb3{ Here rather than  c4  to tie Black down to the defence of  c5  unless that is he now goes in for some slightly premature activity. }
13. c4
14. dxc4{ White is quite happy to take on a passed c-pawn while retaining control of  d5  in the process. }
14. Nxe4
15. Qxd8+
