[Result "*"]

1. Nf3{ Although our setup (the Reti Proper) can transpose from other first moves, 1.  Nf3  is the most reliable way to achieve it. }
1. d5
2. c4{ We waste no time challenging Black's early presence in the centre. }
2. e6
3. e3
3. Nf6
4. Nc3( { A familiar method of development from how we met the Slav.    Here too we activate the knight before going  b2-b3  }{ ( }4.b3 c5 { isn't such a bad version of a Tarrasch for Black). } )( { Now   }4...c6 5.b3 { would, of course, take play back into the realm of the Semi-Slav sidelines  and here we'll focus our coverage on: }( 4...c5  )( 4...dxc4  )( 4...a6  )( 4...Nbd7  )( 4...Be7  ){ A couple of minor options should also be briefly mentioned. } )
4. a6
5. b3{ Our favourite approach, fianchettoing the queen's bishop and always enabling White after  ...dxc4  to maintain control of  d5  with  bxc4 . Now play may yet enter the waters of the  4...Be7  lines  after }( 5...Be7 6.Bb2 { , }{ although Black can also try something a little more creative. } )
5. b6
6. Bb2
6. Bb7
7. cxd5( { A tempting change of approach now that Black's bishop is on  b7 . White angles for a central majority and some pressure down the c-file after }7...Nxd5 8.Rc1 { and also has in mind a quick rehousing of the knight on  c3 . } )
7. exd5
8. Ne2{ Unfurling the dark-squared bishop and so taking firm control of  d4  ahead of untangling the kingside with either  g2 - g3  and  Bg2  or  Ng3 . }
8. Bd6
9. Ng3( { White spies the slightly soft square on  f5  and this is a tempting alternative to the solid and sensible approach that would be }9.g3 { followed by  Bg2  and  O-O . } )
9. g6
10. Rc1{ The rook won't find a better square and now White may be able to obtain some pressure down the c-file in the event of meeting ... c5  with  d2 - d4 . }
10. Nbd7
11. Bd3{ This continued the creative approach in Sunilduth Lyna-Sankalp, Internet  (blitz) 2020. White is now ready to castle and may be able to cause problems against any ... O-O-O  approach from Black with  Qe2 .     The black king may, of course, also go to the kingside when expansion with  Ng5  and  f2 - f4  would be very much a plan. }
