5. b3{ Once a neglected backwater, this has been a pretty topical line of the Reti in recent years thanks to the patronage of Duda, Keymer and Vladislav Artemiev, as well as whole host of the 2700 Club giving it some occasional patronage.     White continues to hold back on  d2 - d4 , while preparing to bring the dark-squared bishop to the long diagonal. Now Black usually continues in typical QGD fashion by castling, although that's by no means forced. }
5. O-O
6. Bb2{ Completing the fianchetto and now Black usually goes in for one of his own or reacts in the centre. As such we'll have a final divide between: }( 6...c5  )( 6...b6  )( 6...dxc4  )
6. b6
7. cxd5{ The choice of Carlsen and Keymer, aiming to clarify the central situation, if by no means White's only option against Black's solid QGD-type set-up. }
7. exd5
8. d4( { Staking a central foothold after all ahead of completing development with  Bd3  and  O-O . White can also remain flexible with }8.Rc1 Bb7 9.Be2 { , }{ but it's a bit hard to believe in }8.Rg1?! c5 { here when the centre is opening much faster than White would wish. } )
8. Bb7
9. Bd3{ All is now set for  O-O , while Black faces a decision: to play ... c5  or not and, if so, with the queen's knight on  d7  or not? }
9. Nbd7
10. O-O( { Now }10...c5 11.Rc1 { transposes to a position we'll consider via a 9... c5  10.O-O  Nbd7  11.Rc1  move order and otherwise White may look to expand with  Ne5 . } )
10. a6
11. Ne5( { White has often preferred to manoeuvre with }11.Rc1 Bd6 12.Ne2 { , }{ but there's no reason not to expand straightaway, thereby introducing the option of  Qf3 , as well as  Ne2  and  Rc1 . } )
11. Nxe5
12. dxe5{ Seizing the initiative, as White will be quick to follow up with  Qc2  and/or  f2 - f4 . }
12. Ne4
13. Qc2( { A consistent and decent alternative to the }13.Ne2!? { of Keymer-Triapishko, Internet (blitz) 2020. } )
13. f5
14. Ne2{ Now this is even stronger than a move earlier. White will begin to home in on Black's weaknesses through  Nf4  and  Rfd1 , with a timely  f2 - f3  also quite a useful resource. }
