12. Bd2{ Completing development and a rapid queenside assault with  b2 - b4 ,  a2 - a4  and  b4 - b5  is now very much on the agenda. }
12. f5
13. b4
13. Bf7
14. f4{ Refusing to allow Black the chance to achieve a fair degree of liberation with ... e5 . }
14. Nf6
15. Be1( { White rushed straight ahead with }15.a4 Ne4 16.b5 { in Milov-Dunis, Cannes 2006, but there's no need to rush so. }{ Instead, we create the option of bringing the bishop round to  h4  and will now meet ... Ne4  with  Na4 , installing the knight with tempo on  b6  ahead of opening lines with  a2 - a4  and  b4 - b5 . } )
