9. c5
10. bxc5{ Opening up the b-file to seize the initiative. }
10. bxc5
11. Rb1
11. Qc7
12. Ba3{ Black is already under considerable pressure, with both  Bxc5  and  dxc5  threatened and White very much also able to consider expanding with gain of tempo through  Nb5  and maybe even  Ne5 . }
