9. b3{ Giving the bishop the option of  a3  as well as  b2 , and White may also wish to try and clamp down on the black queenside with  a2 - a4 - a5 . }
9. b6
10. a4( { Upping the ante, although you might prefer to calmly complete development with }10.Ba3 { and  Qc2 . } )
10. a5
11. Ba3{ There is a hole on  b4  and Black is still pretty solid, but White too could be far from unhappy in Chigaev-Maksimenko, Titled Tuesday Blitz 2022, where the plan was to exert some pressure on Black's position with  Ne5  and  f2 - f4 , possibly in conjunction with  Rc1  and an exchange on  d5 . }
