12. cxd4
13. exd4{ The most dynamic and challenging recapture, aiming to cause problems for Black's knights with  a2 - a3  and  d4 - d5 . There's also the idea of  Ng5  should Black try and bring his bishop to  e6 . }
13. Bc6
14. Bg5{ We've reached a typically unbalanced isolated queen's pawn position, but with White set to activate through  Re1  and  Bc4 , we'd slightly prefer to take his position. Other ideas to bear in mind are the good, old  Qd2  and  Bh6 , as well as  Ne5 . }
