8. d4{ The bishop might be on  e2  rather than  d3  here, but it still makes sense to compete for control of those important central squares,  e5  and  c5 .     Now ... c5  will not only cost Black a tempo, but will result in an isolated queen's pawn after exchanges on  c5  and  d5 . }
