13. Nxe4
14. Qxe4
14. Rb8
15. dxc5{ Continuing to counter with tempo and now White would love to be able to line up his queen and bishop on the long dark-square diagonal. }
15. Bxc5
16. Rab1{ White retains an edge with the more active pieces and safer king. Both  Bd3  and  Qg4  are useful looking attacking ideas, while  Rfd1  or just  Ba1  will help the rooks. }
