10. g4{ Even those of a more positional persuasion should really want to launch so here. Low on counterplay, Black lacks a good way to deal with the threat of  g4 - g5  other than to take the pawn when White will leap forwards with  Ne4 , unfurling our favourite bishop in the process. }
