13. fxe4
14. Rxg4{ Clearly Black will be mated if he's now careless enough to allow White's heavy pieces to land on  g7  and  h7 . }
14. Nf6
15. Rxe4
15. Nxe4
16. Qxe4{ With  Bd3  and  Rg1  on their way, White enjoys an extremely strong attack. }
