17. Qxb1( { Black's active pieces gave him definite compensation in Yurov-Jung, correspondence 2017, which he managed to draw, but White should not be too unhappy here. There's now a definite threat of   }18.d3 { (and if }18...Qa5+ 19.Bb4 { ), and  Bxc5  may also prove a timely exchange.     We can also support the knight on  d5  with  Bc4 , or consider  Nb6 - c4 , and may even get to go  Rg4  should Black's bishop wander off the  h3 - c8  diagonal. In short, the position is pretty messy and Black must be quite accurate to justify the position of his advanced knight duo, accuracy which may not be so easy to achieve at non-correspondence time controls. } )
