12. Rac1( { Simple chess, although we should note that Ivanchuk has preferred }12.Qd1 { and Tomashevsky and Grivas }12.Rfc1 Rfc8 13.Qd1 { here. By placing the queen's rook on the open file White keeps the option of  Qb1  open (the queen may then journey on to  a1  and it would also quite like to land on  f5  should Black make a doubled-edged ... e5  push), while intending  Nfd4 - c6  if Black doesn't contest the queenside. } )
12. Rac8
13. Qb1{ Threatening to take on  c8  then  a7 . }
13. Bxb5
14. Bxb5{ This left White with a pleasant edge in Appel-Fiebig, German Bundesliga 2009.     He threatens to take control of the c-file with  Ba6  and also has ideas of  Nd4 - c6 ,  Ng5 , angling to force a weakness,  Qa1  and just  Rc2  followed by  Rfc1 . }
