11. Rfd1
11. Qe7
12. Rac1{ Completing development. Here a quick  e3 - e4  may result in exchanges and a pretty solid position for Black, who will equalise with a timely ... c5 .     As such, White shouldn't rush, with one decent plan that of preparing to contest the  h1 - a8  diagonal with  Bf1  and  g2 - g3 . }
12. Rac8
13. g3
13. dxc4
