15. h3{ White also wants to take control of  g4 , continuing to ask Black just what their plan is. }
15. Bd7
16. Rfe1{ Never a bad square for a rook in this structure as White's position remained the easier to play in Kovalevskaya-Ivakhinova, Ekaterinburg 2013. If allowed White would now like to go  Bf1  and  Rad1  ahead of carrying out a powerful central advance in  e3 - e4  followed by  d3 - d4 . }
