19. Rxf7
20. Qxg6
20. Rg7( 20...Nxe5!? 21.Qh5+ Kg8 22.Qxe5 { White is a clear pawn to the good and Black surely won't manage to survive with such an open king and undeveloped queenside. For example: }22...Qh4 23.Qe2 ( 23.g3!? Qf6 24.Bf4 Qxe5 25.Bxe5 { With  Be4  on the way and/or Harry all set to advance, Black is surely positionally lost. } )Kf8 24.Rd3 { And White enjoys a very strong, ongoing initiative. } )
